g", "work_id": 81068, "role": "director", "role_id": 938, "is_primary": true}, {"id": 2227233, "title": "Fanny and Alexander", "work_id": 83155, "role": "director", "role_id": 938, "is_primary": true}, {"id": 2650398, "title": "Sommaren med Monika = Summer with Monika", "work_id": 115673, "role": "director", "role_id": 938, "is_primary": true}, {"id": 2227275, "title": "Fanny and Alexander = Fanny och Alexander", "work_id": 83156, "role": "director", "role_id": 938, "is_primary": true}, {"id": 792091, "title": "Images: my life in film (Text)", "work_id": 86118, "role": "author", "role_id": 943, "is_primary": true}, {"id": 2263133, "title": "Scenes from a marriage", "work_id": 86132, "role": "producer/director", "role_id": 31, "is_primary": true}, {"id": 2650401, "title": "Viskingar och rop = Cries and whispers", "work_id": 115674, "role": "producer/director", "role_id": 31, "is_primary": true}, {"id": 2284036, "title": "The Touch", "work_id": 85489, "role": "producer/director", "role_id": 31, "is_primary": true}, {"id": 2292955, "title": "Torment = Hets", "work_id": 86498, "role": "writer", "role_id": 939, "is_primary": true}, {"id": 2225626, "title": "Faithless = Trolosa [Widescreen]", "work_id": 92613, "role": "writer", "role_id": 939, "is_primary": true}], "also_known_as": "Ernst Ingmar Bergman", "date_of_birth": "1918-07-14", "date_of_death": "2007-07-30", "genders": [{"id": 9, "name": "Male", "slug": "male"}], "languages": [{"id": 5, "name": "German", "slug": "german"}, {"id": 35, "name": "Swedish", "slug": "swedish"}], "places_of_operation": [{"id": 43, "name": "Sweden", "slug": "sweden"}], "biography": "Ernst Ingmar Bergman (14 July 1918 – 30 July 2007) was a Swedish film director, screenwriter, producer and playwright. Widely considered one of the most accomplished and influential filmmakers of all time, Bergman's films are known as \"profoundly personal meditations into the myriad struggles facing the psyche and the soul.\"Bergman directed more than 60 films and documentaries for cinematic release and for television screenings, most of which he also wrote. His theatrical career continued in parallel and included periods as Leading Director of the Royal Dramatic Theatre in Stockholm and of the Residenztheater in Munich. He directed more than 170 plays. He forged a creative partnership with his cinematographers Gunnar Fischer and Sven Nykvist. Among his company of actors were Harriet Andersson, Bibi Andersson, Liv Ullmann, Gunnar Björnstrand, Erland Josephson, Ingrid Thulin, and Max von Sydow. Most of his films were set in Sweden, and many films from Through a Glass Darkly (1961) onward were filmed on the island of Fårö.\nPhilip French referred to Bergman as \"one of the greatest artists of the 20th century ... he found in literature and the performing arts a way of both recreating and questioning the human condition.\" Director Martin Scorsese commented that \"it's impossible to overestimate the effect that [his] films had on people.\" Bergman was ranked 8th in director's poll on Sight & Sound's 2002 list of The Greatest Directors of All Time.", "biography_author": "Wikidata", "date_of_biography": "2022-05-19T11:47:43.712700+10:00", "external_links": [{"id": 2260, "uri": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ingmar_Bergman"}], "uuid": "4261ee1e-812c-4e6b-a75e-63375e23ae88", "source": {"name": "Vernon", "slug": "vernon"}, "source_identifier": "255", "external_references": [{"id": 9706, "source": {"name": "Wikidata", "slug": "wikidata"}, "source_identifier": "Q7546"}, {"id": 9707, "source": {"name": "VIAF", "slug": "viaf"}, "source_identifier": "110097018"}, {"id": 9708, "source": {"name": "LOC Auth", "slug": "loc-auth"}, "source_identifier": "n79054388"}, {"id": 9709, "source": {"name": "WorldCat", "slug": "worldcat"}, "source_identifier": "lccn-n79054388"}], "date_modified": "2025-03-05T14:20:53.936950+11:00"}, {"id": 10134, "name": "Neil Jordan", "roles_in_work": [{"id": 904745, "title": "Interview with a vampire: the vampire chronicles (S)", "work_id": 85582, "role": "director", "role_id": 938, "is_primary": true}], "also_known_as": "Neil Patrick Jordan", "date_of_birth": "1950-02-25", "date_of_death": null, "genders": [{"id": 9, "name": "Male", "slug": "male"}], "languages": [{"id": 1, "name": "English", "slug": "english"}], "places_of_operation": [{"id": 294, "name": "Republic of Ireland", "slug": "republic-of-ireland"}], "biography": "Neil Patrick Jordan (born 25 February 1950) is an Irish film director, screenwriter, novelist and short-story writer. His first book, Night in Tunisia, won a Somerset Maugham Award and the Guardian Fiction Prize in 1979. He won an Academy Award (Best Original Screenplay) for The Crying Game (1992). He has also won three Irish Film and Television Awards, as well as the Golden Lion at the Venice International Film Festival for Michael Collins (1996) and the Silver Bear for Best Director at the Berlin International Film Festival for The Butcher Boy (1997).\nJordan also created The Borgias (2011 TV series) for Showtime.", "biography_author": "Wikidata", "date_of_biography": "2022-05-19T12:34:29.562088+10:00", "external_links": [{"id": 2772, "uri": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Neil_Jordan"}], "uuid": "27c0be07-0f74-4b34-b024-b39a8c3218ba", "source": {"name": "Vernon", "slug": "vernon"}, "source_identifier": "120", "external_references": [{"id": 11810, "source": {"name": "Wikidata", "slug": "wikidata"}, "source_identifier": "Q55428"}, {"id": 11811, "source": {"name": "VIAF", "slug": "viaf"}, "source_identifier": "85368254"}, {"id": 11812, "source": {"name": "LOC Auth", "slug": "loc-auth"}, "source_identifier": "n79138918"}, {"id": 11813, "source": {"name": "WorldCat", "slug": "worldcat"}, "source_identifier": "lccn-n79138918"}], "date_modified": "2023-09-13T12:31:35.458346+10:00"}, {"id": 10132, "name": "Ian Irvine", "roles_in_work": [{"id": 2639921, "title": "Splintered", "work_id": 110558, "role": "writer", "role_id": 939, "is_primary": true}], "also_kn